## Purpose

Define the Bubble Tea message types that enable communication between the BackgroundWorker goroutine and the UI's Update() loop. These messages are the ONLY way data flows from background to UI.

## Message Definitions

```go
package ui

// SnapshotReadyMsg is sent by BackgroundWorker when a new snapshot is ready.
// The UI should swap its current snapshot pointer to this new one.
//
// This is the primary data transfer mechanism. The snapshot is immutable
// and safe to read without locks.
//
// Processing this message should be O(1) - just a pointer swap.
// All expensive work has already been done in the background.
type SnapshotReadyMsg struct {
    // Snapshot is the new, fully-populated, immutable data snapshot.
    // Contains: Issues, IssueMap, Stats, all pre-computed view data.
    Snapshot *DataSnapshot
}

// Phase2UpdateMsg is sent when Phase 2 analysis completes.
// The UI should update any views that depend on Phase 2 metrics
// (PageRank, Betweenness, HITS, etc.)
//
// Note: The snapshot's Stats field is already updated by the time
// this message arrives. This message just signals "it's ready now."
type Phase2UpdateMsg struct {
    // Version identifies which snapshot this update applies to.
    // If the UI has moved to a newer snapshot, this update can be ignored.
    Version uint64

    // Stats contains the updated GraphStats with Phase 2 fields populated.
    // This is the same pointer as in the snapshot, just for convenience.
    Stats *analysis.GraphStats
}

// SnapshotErrorMsg is sent if snapshot building fails.
// The UI should display an error state but continue operating
// with the previous snapshot.
type SnapshotErrorMsg struct {
    Err error

    // Recoverable indicates whether the error is transient.
    // true = file temporarily unavailable, will retry
    // false = configuration error, needs user intervention
    Recoverable bool
}

// RefreshRequestMsg is sent FROM the UI TO trigger a refresh.
// Used when user changes recipe, requests manual refresh, etc.
//
// This is handled by the BackgroundWorker, not by Update().
type RefreshRequestMsg struct {
    // Force indicates whether to reload even if file unchanged.
    Force bool

    // Recipe specifies filter/sort configuration to apply.
    // If nil, uses current/default recipe.
    Recipe *recipe.Recipe
}
```

