# Double-Tap CapsLock Detection

## Background
User can single-tap CapsLock for full tutorial, or double-tap quickly for context-specific help. This requires timing logic.

## Algorithm

\`\`\`go
type tutorialTrigger struct {
    lastCapsLockTime time.Time
    pendingTimer     bool
}

const doubleTapThreshold = 300 * time.Millisecond

// Called when CapsLock detected
func (t *tutorialTrigger) handleCapsLock() tea.Cmd {
    now := time.Now()

    if t.pendingTimer && now.Sub(t.lastCapsLockTime) < doubleTapThreshold {
        // Double tap detected!
        t.pendingTimer = false
        return showContextHelpCmd()
    }

    // First tap - start timer
    t.lastCapsLockTime = now
    t.pendingTimer = true

    return tea.Tick(doubleTapThreshold, func(time.Time) tea.Msg {
        return capsLockTimerExpiredMsg{}
    })
}

// Called when timer expires without second tap
func (t *tutorialTrigger) handleTimerExpired() tea.Cmd {
    if t.pendingTimer {
        t.pendingTimer = false
        return showFullTutorialCmd()
    }
    return nil
}
\`\`\`

## Message Types
\`\`\`go
type showTutorialMsg struct {
    contextOnly bool
    context     string  // Current context if contextOnly
}

type capsLockTimerExpiredMsg struct{}
\`\`\`

## Edge Cases
- User holds CapsLock (should be single trigger, not repeated)
- User triple-taps (treat as double-tap, then ignore third)
- Timer expires exactly as second tap comes in (prefer double-tap)

## Integration
In main Model.Update():
