# Port TopK Set Algorithm

## Context
TopK Set finds the k issues that, when completed, maximize the total downstream unlocks. Uses greedy submodular optimization.

## Go Implementation Reference
```go
// generateTopKSet in advanced_insights.go
// Greedy selection maximizing marginal unlocks
```

## Rust Implementation (advanced/topk_set.rs)
```rust
use crate::graph::DiGraph;
use crate::whatif;

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct TopKSetItem {
    pub node: usize,
    pub marginal_gain: usize,
}

pub struct TopKSetResult {
    pub items: Vec<TopKSetItem>,
    pub total_gain: usize,
}

/// Greedy submodular selection for maximum unlock.
pub fn topk_set(graph: &DiGraph, closed_set: &[bool], k: usize) -> TopKSetResult {
    let n = graph.node_count();
    let mut selected = Vec::new();
    let mut current_closed = closed_set.to_vec();
    let mut total_gain = 0;

    for _ in 0..k {
        // Find node with maximum marginal gain
        let mut best_node = None;
        let mut best_gain = 0;

        for v in 0..n {
            if current_closed[v] { continue; }

            let result = whatif::what_if_close(graph, v, &current_closed);
            if result.transitive_unblocks > best_gain {
                best_gain = result.transitive_unblocks;
                best_node = Some(v);
            }
        }

        match best_node {
            Some(node) => {
                selected.push(TopKSetItem {
                    node,
                    marginal_gain: best_gain,
                });
                current_closed[node] = true;
                total_gain += best_gain;
            }
            None => break, // No more beneficial nodes
        }
    }

    TopKSetResult {
        items: selected,
        total_gain,
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Greedy selection maximizes total gain
- [ ] Returns k items (or fewer if exhausted)
- [ ] Marginal gains decrease monotonically

# Implement Reachability Queries

## Context
Reachability queries find all nodes reachable from/to a given node. Essential for impact analysis and dependency exploration.

## Rust Implementation (reachability.rs)
```rust
use crate::graph::DiGraph;
use std::collections::VecDeque;

/// Find all nodes reachable from source (BFS forward).
pub fn reachable_from(graph: &DiGraph, source: usize) -> Vec<usize> {
    let n = graph.node_count();
    if source >= n {
        return Vec::new();
    }

    let mut visited = vec![false; n];
    let mut queue = VecDeque::new();
    let mut result = Vec::new();

    queue.push_back(source);
    visited[source] = true;

    while let Some(v) = queue.pop_front() {
        result.push(v);
        for &w in graph.successors(v) {
            if !visited[w] {
                visited[w] = true;
                queue.push_back(w);
            }
        }
    }

    result
}

/// Find all nodes that can reach target (BFS backward).
pub fn reachable_to(graph: &DiGraph, target: usize) -> Vec<usize> {
    let n = graph.node_count();
    if target >= n {
        return Vec::new();
    }

    let mut visited = vec![false; n];
    let mut queue = VecDeque::new();
    let mut result = Vec::new();

    queue.push_back(target);
    visited[target] = true;

    while let Some(v) = queue.pop_front() {
        result.push(v);
        for &u in graph.predecessors(v) {
            if !visited[u] {
                visited[u] = true;
                queue.push_back(u);
            }
        }
    }

    result
}

/// Get direct blockers (predecessors) of a node.
pub fn blockers(graph: &DiGraph, node: usize) -> Vec<usize> {
    graph.predecessors(node).to_vec()
}

/// Get direct dependents (successors) of a node.
pub fn dependents(graph: &DiGraph, node: usize) -> Vec<usize> {
    graph.successors(node).to_vec()
}

/// Check if all predecessors of node are in closed_set.
pub fn is_actionable(graph: &DiGraph, node: usize, closed_set: &[bool]) -> bool {
    graph.predecessors(node).iter().all(|&p| {
        closed_set.get(p).copied().unwrap_or(false)
    })
}

/// Get all actionable nodes (no open blockers).
pub fn actionable_nodes(graph: &DiGraph, closed_set: &[bool]) -> Vec<usize> {
    (0..graph.node_count())
        .filter(|&i| !closed_set.get(i).copied().unwrap_or(false))
        .filter(|&i| is_actionable(graph, i, closed_set))
        .collect()
}
