# Implement Local Preview Server with Hot Reload

## Context
Users need to preview their static site locally before deploying. This requires a simple HTTP server with some nice-to-have features like watching for changes.

## Requirements

### Basic Server
```go
// pkg/export/preview.go

type PreviewServer struct {
    bundlePath string
    port       int
    server     *http.Server
    watcher    *fsnotify.Watcher
    clients    map[chan bool]bool // SSE clients for hot reload
    mu         sync.Mutex
}

func NewPreviewServer(bundlePath string, port int) *PreviewServer {
    return &PreviewServer{
        bundlePath: bundlePath,
        port:       port,
        clients:    make(map[chan bool]bool),
    }
}

func (p *PreviewServer) Start() error {
    mux := http.NewServeMux()

    // Static file server
    fs := http.FileServer(http.Dir(p.bundlePath))
    mux.Handle("/", noCache(fs))

    // SSE endpoint for hot reload
    mux.HandleFunc("/__preview__/events", p.sseHandler)

    // Status endpoint
    mux.HandleFunc("/__preview__/status", p.statusHandler)

    p.server = &http.Server{
        Addr:    fmt.Sprintf(":%d", p.port),
        Handler: mux,
    }

    return p.server.ListenAndServe()
}
```

### No-Cache Middleware
Ensure browsers always get fresh content during preview:
```go
func noCache(next http.Handler) http.Handler {
    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
        w.Header().Set("Cache-Control", "no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate")
        w.Header().Set("Pragma", "no-cache")
        w.Header().Set("Expires", "0")
        next.ServeHTTP(w, r)
    })
}
```

### Hot Reload via SSE
```go
func (p *PreviewServer) sseHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "text/event-stream")
    w.Header().Set("Cache-Control", "no-cache")
    w.Header().Set("Connection", "keep-alive")

    notify := make(chan bool)
    p.mu.Lock()
    p.clients[notify] = true
    p.mu.Unlock()

    defer func() {
        p.mu.Lock()
        delete(p.clients, notify)
        p.mu.Unlock()
    }()

    for {
        select {
        case <-notify:
            fmt.Fprintf(w, "data: reload\n\n")
            w.(http.Flusher).Flush()
        case <-r.Context().Done():
            return
        }
    }
}

func (p *PreviewServer) notifyClients() {
    p.mu.Lock()
    defer p.mu.Unlock()
    for ch := range p.clients {
        select {
        case ch <- true:
        default:
        }
    }
}
```

### File Watcher
```go
func (p *PreviewServer) StartWatcher() error {
    watcher, err := fsnotify.NewWatcher()
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }
    p.watcher = watcher

    go func() {
        for {
            select {
            case event := <-watcher.Events:
                if event.Op&(fsnotify.Write|fsnotify.Create) != 0 {
                    p.notifyClients()
                }
            case err := <-watcher.Errors:
                log.Printf("watcher error: %v", err)
            }
        }
    }()

    // Watch data directory
    return watcher.Add(filepath.Join(p.bundlePath, "data"))
}
```

### Viewer Integration
Add SSE client to viewer.js:
```javascript
// Only in preview mode (detect via /__preview__/status)
if (window.location.hostname === 'localhost' || window.location.hostname === '127.0.0.1') {
    const eventSource = new EventSource('/__preview__/events');
    eventSource.onmessage = (event) => {
        if (event.data === 'reload') {
            window.location.reload();
        }
    };
}
```

### Interactive Controls
When running preview from wizard:
```
Preview server running at http://localhost:9000

Keyboard controls:
  r - Force refresh (regenerate export)
  d - Deploy to GitHub Pages
  q - Quit preview

Press 'r' to regenerate, 'd' to deploy, or 'q' to quit...
```

### Port Selection
```go
func findAvailablePort(start, end int) (int, error) {
    for port := start; port <= end; port++ {
        listener, err := net.Listen("tcp", fmt.Sprintf(":%d", port))
        if err == nil {
            listener.Close()
            return port, nil
        }
    }
    return 0, fmt.Errorf("no available port in range %d-%d", start, end)
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Server starts and serves bundle
- [ ] No-cache headers prevent stale content
- [ ] Browser auto-opens on start
- [ ] SSE hot reload works when files change
- [ ] 'r' key regenerates export
- [ ] 'd' key triggers deployment flow
- [ ] 'q' key cleanly exits
- [ ] Auto-selects available port if default in use
- [ ] Works on macOS, Linux, Windows

## Notes
- Keep dependencies minimal (just std lib + fsnotify)
- SSE is simpler than WebSocket for this use case
- Hot reload is nice-to-have, not critical for MVP

# Implement gh CLI Integration for GitHub Pages Deployment

## Context
Integration with GitHub's `gh` CLI tool to create repositories, push content, and enable GitHub Pages - matching the approach used in mcp_agent_mail.

## Requirements

### Detection and Installation
```go
// pkg/export/github.go

func CheckGHInstalled() (bool, error) {
    _, err := exec.LookPath("gh")
    return err == nil, nil
}

func CheckGHAuthenticated() (bool, string, error) {
    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "auth", "status")
    output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()
    // Parse output for username
    return err == nil, parseUsername(output), nil
}

func InstallGH() error {
    // Detect package manager
    switch detectPackageManager() {
    case "brew":
        return exec.Command("brew", "install", "gh").Run()
    case "apt":
        // Show manual instructions
        return fmt.Errorf("Run: curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/...")
    default:
        return fmt.Errorf("Install gh CLI from: https://cli.github.com/")
    }
}

func AuthenticateGH() error {
    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "auth", "login")
    cmd.Stdin = os.Stdin
    cmd.Stdout = os.Stdout
    cmd.Stderr = os.Stderr
    return cmd.Run()
}
```

### Repository Operations
```go
func CreateRepository(name string, private bool, description string) (string, error) {
    visibility := "--public"
    if private {
        visibility = "--private"
    }

    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "repo", "create", name,
        visibility,
        "--description", description,
        "--clone=false",
    )

    if err := cmd.Run(); err != nil {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to create repository: %w", err)
    }

    // Get full repo name (owner/repo)
    return getRepoFullName(name)
}

func getRepoFullName(name string) (string, error) {
    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "repo", "view", name,
        "--json", "nameWithOwner",
        "-q", ".nameWithOwner",
    )
    output, err := cmd.Output()
    return strings.TrimSpace(string(output)), err
}

func RepoExists(name string) bool {
    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "repo", "view", name)
    return cmd.Run() == nil
}
```

### Git Operations
```go
func InitAndPush(bundlePath string, repoFullName string) error {
    // Initialize git repo
    cmds := [][]string{
        {"git", "init"},
        {"git", "add", "."},
        {"git", "commit", "-m", "Initial static site export"},
        {"git", "branch", "-M", "main"},
        {"git", "remote", "add", "origin", 
            fmt.Sprintf("https://github.com/%s.git", repoFullName)},
        {"git", "push", "-u", "origin", "main", "--force"},
    }

    for _, args := range cmds {
        cmd := exec.Command(args[0], args[1:]...)
        cmd.Dir = bundlePath
        if output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {
            return fmt.Errorf("%s failed: %s", args[0], output)
        }
    }

    return nil
}
```

### Enable GitHub Pages
```go
func EnableGitHubPages(repoFullName string) (string, error) {
    // Enable Pages via API
    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "api",
        fmt.Sprintf("repos/%s/pages", repoFullName),
        "-X", "POST",
        "-f", "source[branch]=main",
        "-f", "source[path]=/",
    )

    if output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {
        // Check if already enabled
        if strings.Contains(string(output), "already exists") {
            // Pages already enabled, get URL
            return getGitHubPagesURL(repoFullName)
        }
        return "", fmt.Errorf("failed to enable Pages: %s", output)
    }

    // Wait for Pages to be configured
    time.Sleep(2 * time.Second)

    return getGitHubPagesURL(repoFullName)
}

func getGitHubPagesURL(repoFullName string) (string, error) {
    cmd := exec.Command("gh", "api",
        fmt.Sprintf("repos/%s/pages", repoFullName),
        "-q", ".html_url",
    )
    output, err := cmd.Output()
    if err != nil {
        // Construct URL manually as fallback
        parts := strings.Split(repoFullName, "/")
        return fmt.Sprintf("https://%s.github.io/%s/", parts[0], parts[1]), nil
    }
    return strings.TrimSpace(string(output)), nil
}
```

### High-Level Deploy Function
```go
type GitHubDeployConfig struct {
    RepoName        string
    Private         bool
    Description     string
    BundlePath      string
}

func DeployToGitHubPages(config GitHubDeployConfig) (string, error) {
    // 1. Check/install gh CLI
    if installed, _ := CheckGHInstalled(); !installed {
        if err := InstallGH(); err != nil {
            return "", err
        }
    }

    // 2. Check/perform authentication
    if authed, _, _ := CheckGHAuthenticated(); !authed {
        if err := AuthenticateGH(); err != nil {
            return "", err
        }
    }

    // 3. Create repository (or use existing)
    repoFullName, err := CreateRepository(config.RepoName, config.Private, config.Description)
    if err != nil {
        if RepoExists(config.RepoName) {
            repoFullName, _ = getRepoFullName(config.RepoName)
        } else {
            return "", err
        }
    }

    // 4. Initialize git and push
    if err := InitAndPush(config.BundlePath, repoFullName); err != nil {
        return "", err
    }

    // 5. Enable GitHub Pages
    pagesURL, err := EnableGitHubPages(repoFullName)
    if err != nil {
        return "", err
    }

    return pagesURL, nil
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Detects gh CLI installation
- [ ] Offers to install via brew (macOS)
- [ ] Shows manual instructions for Linux
- [ ] Checks and triggers authentication
- [ ] Creates public/private repositories
- [ ] Handles existing repository gracefully
- [ ] Pushes bundle contents to repo
- [ ] Enables GitHub Pages via API
- [ ] Returns correct Pages URL
- [ ] Handles network errors gracefully

## Testing
- Mock exec.Command for unit tests
- Integration test with real gh CLI (optional, manual)
- Test error paths (no network, auth failed, etc.)

