## Objective

Implement a high-performance Rust-WASM version of HybridScorer for large datasets (>5000 issues) where JavaScript performance becomes a bottleneck.

## Background

For typical bv usage (<1000 issues), JavaScript is sufficient. However, large enterprise projects may have 5000+ issues where:
- Re-ranking 5000 results on preset change could take >100ms in JS
- Users expect instant (<16ms) UI response
- Mobile browsers have weaker JS performance

Rust compiled to WASM provides:
- 10-50x faster numeric computation than JS
- SIMD optimizations for batch scoring
- Consistent performance across browsers

## When to Use

This is OPTIONAL. Use the JS implementation by default and only load WASM for:
- Datasets >5000 issues
- Performance-critical deployments
- Mobile-first use cases

